owing Ozon’s importance for a thoroughly postmodern filmgoing generation to be given the attention it deserves.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture producers and directorszFrance. 0aMotion pictureszFrance. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  a8 femmes.  aFrancois Ozon.  aGouttes d'eau sur pierres brûlantes.  aLes Amants criminels.  aRegarde la mer.  aadult sexualities.  ahorror.  akinship.  amelodrama.  amusic.  asexual desire.  aspectral carcasses.  aviolence.1 aAsibong, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614140840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526141408423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526141408/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles